free: #e When you come here, I hope that you can at least stay overnight at times.
#c 你來這裡，至少也在這裡過一夜。
#n T 和M 是親戚，M 經常來台北出差，T的意思是既然常來，怎麼樣也至少去他家坐坐。
#e Moreover, so much work... I cannot do so as I wish; so much work in TapangU.
#c 而且有很多工作...我不能照我想的...達邦有很多工作。
#e Let's see...if (I) have a little time, (I) can stay overnight and look around (Taipei).
#c 這個嘛... 如果我有一點時間我就可以過夜在台北到處看看。
#e When I arrive here, I feel surprised at people in Taipei.
#c 當我來到這裡，台北的人讓我很驚訝。
#n eatatapihu '在台北的人'是定型化片語名詞，構詞為 ea-ta-taipahu 在-斜格-台北
#e Right. There are many people here.
#c 對，這裡真的有很多人。
#e On that morning I took an airplane.
#c 早上我坐飛機。
#e Really?
#c 真的?
#e Although I left very early, I felt amazed that there are a lot of people there.
#c 雖然很早，我很驚訝怎麼那麼多人。
#e The very large airplane on that morning was almost full.
#c 早上那個很大的飛機幾乎坐滿。
#e The teacher said it seems that there're quite a lot of people on the airplane today.
#c 台大的教授說今天的飛機似乎人很多。
#n Teacher here refers to a professor at NTU.
#e I also said, this is really...
#c 我也說,這個真的是...
#e When I came here last time, there were not so many like this.
#c 我上次來這裡沒有這麼多人。
#e Fortunately, (you) got a seat.
#c 很幸運,有位置。
#e My seat has been reserved in advance by the people here.
#c 啊...那是事先... 這裡的人是先幫我預定了位置。
#e Therefore I will not be afraid of being without a seat when I go back and forth.
#c 因此我來回坐不怕沒有位置。
#n 此IU開頭有 'a isi [EVI AUX.NAF] 應較完整。
#n 此IU開頭有 'a isi [EVI AUX.NAF] 應較完整。
#e My seat for going home in the evening has already been reserved.
#c 我晚上回家的位置已經預定了。
#e The back and forth in one day is really exhausting.
#c 一天之內來回真的非常累。
#e If I cannot (answer the question) they really want to ask about Tsou, it will be a joke.
#c 真是開玩笑如果我不能真的回答他們想問的關於說鄒語的問題。
#n 這句話是由幾個不完整的據子片段拼湊出的，其語意是參酌整體與上下文推論得出的
#e How could it be possible that you can't? If you cannot (do it well), who else can do it?
#c 你怎麼有可能不會？如果連你都不行，還有誰能？

gloss: 照上下文推論應該是一個受焦動詞
free: #e What I teach is short (sentences).
#c 我教的是短的(句子)。
#n '教'這個動詞常出現的形是ma'cohio (主焦) pa'cohivi(處焦)(Tung 1964:488)
#e There are many people asking questions. The situation is like this: there are many people surrounding me; what they asked is so complicated.
#c 有很多人問我問題。他們問的內容很複雜，問的情況就像這樣很多人圍著我。
#e I try to understandt, at least I am able to answer, that is to clarify what they really want to know.
#c 我試著去瞭解，至少我能去回答，也就是弄清楚他們真的想要知道的。
#e I try my best to answer what they want to ask with my limited knowledge.
#c 我盡我最大的努力，用我稍微知道的一點知識，去回答他們想問我的。
#e They should really understand what you've told them.
#c 他們應該真的知道你所告訴他們的。
#e You know a lot.
#c 你知道的很多。
#e It's lucky that what they want to ask will be written down in advance, therefore, I can see them in advance when I come here.
#c 很幸運他們要問的都事先寫下來，因此我來這裡的時候可以先看。
#e Therefore I think maybe I can answer what they want to ask and what they want to know. They will.
#c 因此，我想或許我能回答他們想問的和他們想知道的。他們會。
#e What if those of you work together at the Mu-yu-kong-cua-shi come here and act as informants? I wonder if there'd be any difference.
#c 如果讓跟你一起在母語工作室工作的伙伴也來這裡當發音人會怎麼樣？我在想有什麼差別嗎？
#e (It will depend on) if they will be accepted by the research group here.
#c (那要看)在這裡做研究的會不會接受他們。
#e It's because their funding to invite people for them to ask (Tsou imformants) is probably limited.
#c 或許是因為他們用來邀請讓他們問問題的人（鄒語發音人）的經費有限制。
#e Therefore, the (informants) invited may not be a lot.
#c 因此，能請的發音人不多。
#e Do you have any other ideas if (they) ask you about your opinion on Tsou?
#c 你有沒有其他的想法當你來到這裡讓他們問鄒語的問題?
#e Yes, indeed. Because what I heard is very different....
#c 有啊，真的. 因為我聽到的特別不一樣。
#e They asked many sayings and, they should really know many of this so-called ways of expression.
#c 他們問很多講法。他們應該真的知道許多這種所謂的講法。
#e Especially (those) words linked together.
#c 特別是這些字連起來。
#n 此處說者指的應是指構詞(morphology)。
#n IU120開頭應有 mo c'o [AUX.AF only]。
#e (we have to know how to put together) the position of every word. This is what we really know when we came here.
#c 每個字放的位置...這是我們來這裡真的知道的。
#e If we follow how they really wanted to study Tsou, as I once said, this should be the first things that we should understand.
#c 如果我們依照他們想研究鄒語的方式，就像我剛才說的，這是我們必須先知道的事。
#e (If) The so-called real expressions of Tsou words can be collected all together (like this),
#c (如果)所謂的真正的鄒語的用法中的字能夠（像這樣）被收集起來。
#e Therefore, when I come here, I'm quite touched when I think and know many ways (methods) of dealing with speaking Tsou.
#c 因此，當我來這裡，我很感動當我思考並且知道許當方法處理關於怎麼說鄒語。
#e This is really the advantage of coming here.
#c 這就是來這裡的好處。
#e How about if you let them know the contents of the Tsou books you are making, after you finish them?
#c 等你完成了你在撰寫的鄒語的書，也讓他們知道，如何？
#e It will be terrific if they could realize/know the book I gave to them.
#c 如果他們能夠瞭解我給他們的書，那真的很好。
#e Like the words (we said) when we act in the drama, I already gave them one copy, and said 'You try to read (this).'
#c 像我們在戲裡演的台詞，我已經給他們了，並且說，你們讀讀看。
#e There are many conversations (in the script), if these conversations could be known, then various ways of expressions can be known.
#c (劇本裡)有很多對話，如果能知道這些對話，那個就能知道各種的說法。
#e (I) don't know whether they can.... (For those who) want to practice our Tsou language, there are many (things) which they can select what they want to know (according to their needs).
#c 我不知道他們能不能... 對那些想要研究鄒語的人而言，有很多是他們能夠選擇想要知道的。
#e Those which can be written down are many, (like) we can use Tsou words to write down various legends of Tsou and other people.
#c 能被寫下來的有很多，（像是）我們能用鄒語去寫各種鄒族還有其他族的傳說故事。
#e I think if the time we could use is enough,
#c 我想如果我們時間夠的話,
#e I think (we should) start like this, that is to unify the so-called our own language.
#c 我想（我們應該）這樣開始，使我們自己的語言一致。
#n tonsoha maitan'e = this year
#n tonsoha maitan'e = this year
#e We work more often, like the dictionary, perhaps we frequently think together. we could at least probably complete the materials we have discussed today this year.
#c 我們經常做，像字典，我們經常一起想，我們或許至少可以完成今年以來像現在在討論的部分。
#e At least put words like this all together and therefore (we) can...
#c 至少像這樣把字放在一起，因此我們能...
#e This could be used as the reading materials for the so-called youth.
#c 這個可以當作年輕人的讀物。
#e As for other things (things besides previous mentioned), (we) should constantly increase our lexicon at the same time with doing the conversation materials.'
#c 至於其他的事（除了前面提到的），（我們）應該同時持續的增加我們的字彙，當我們在收集會話的資料。
#e This is really what we said we will face and work hard for this year.
#c 這些是我們說我們今年要面對並且努力去做的。
#e What will you call the so-called dictionary, that is, what's the name of your book?
#c 你怎麼叫我們所謂的字典，就是說，你的書的書名是什麼？
#e I do not really know how to name the book.
#c 我真的不知道怎麼去命名。
#e If (we) name it huo'omza tposʉ, it does not seem to fully express the real intention (behind the book).
#c 如果（我們）叫它huo'omza tposʉ,好像並不能真的代表真正的含意。
#e Let's (temporarily) call it huo' omza ta e'e no cou ( Tsou texts).
#c （我們）還是先叫它huo' omza ta e'e no cou。
#e when I once went abroad and walked around, there are many faraway aborigines like us do the same thing like you.
#c 我去外國走走參觀的時候，有很多像我們一樣的原住民在做像你一樣做的事情。
#e We will listen (pay attention to) when they are making.
#c 當他們在做的時候，我們會好好聽（注意）。
#e There was a (man) from America, (but he) did not show us (what he's doing).
#c 有一個從美國來的...他沒有讓(我們)看（他做的）。
#n This IU contains uncertain hearing, and needs to be rechecked.
#n This IU contains uncertain hearing, and needs to be rechecked.
#n This IU contains uncertain hearing, and needs to be rechecked.
#n This IU contains uncertain hearing, and needs to be rechecked.
#e Like Father Tsai, XXXXX, he intends to make a dictionary as well.
#c 像蔡神父，XXXXX，他也想要做字典。
#e Is this different from your work?
#c 這個和你的工作不同嗎？
#e No, (they)...
#n need to be checked.
#n need to be checked.
#e Because we do not see what father Tasi made, we do not know how it differs.
#c 因為我們沒看到蔡神父做的，我們不知道怎麼不一樣。
#e Doesn't he intend to combine your works?
#c 他不想把你們做的也包含進去嗎？
#e Who knows? (It is) because we never meet and discuss situations like this.
#c 誰知道？因為我們沒有見面討論過這個事。
#e We would appreciate it if he could give us (a copy of his work).
#c 我們會感激如果他能給我們（一本他的著作）。
#e He gave us a book containing alphabetically listed words.
#c 他給了我們一本書，上面是按字母排的生詞。
#e Then he once said that he will (make use of) what they have done (so far) and compile a Tsou dictionary.
#c 他說過他會用他們（到目前為止）做的來編一個鄒語字典。
